{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/CondProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"waitUntil","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"MutexT"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"mutex"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MutexT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"endTime","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gint64","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gint64"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexT"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"MutexProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MutexProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib13MutexProtocolP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_cond_wait()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" it is possible that a spurious or stolen wakeup","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"could occur.  For that reason, waiting on a condition variable should","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"always be in a loop, based on an explicitly-checked predicate.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" is returned if the condition variable was signalled (or in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"case of a spurious wakeup).  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" is returned if ","type":"text"},{"code":"endTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following code shows how to correctly perform a timed wait on a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"condition variable (extending the example presented in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"documentation for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Cond"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["gpointer","pop_data_timed (void)","{","  gint64 end_time;","  gpointer data;","","  g_mutex_lock (&data_mutex);","","  end_time = g_get_monotonic_time () + 5 * G_TIME_SPAN_SECOND;","  while (!current_data)","    if (!g_cond_wait_until (&data_cond, &data_mutex, end_time))","      {","        \/\/ timeout has passed.","        g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","        return NULL;","      }","","  \/\/ there is data for us","  data = current_data;","  current_data = NULL;","","  g_mutex_unlock (&data_mutex);","","  return data;","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Notice that the end time is calculated once, before entering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"loop and reused.  This is the motivation behind the use of absolute"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time on this API – if a relative time of 5 seconds were passed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directly to the call and a spurious wakeup occurred, the program would","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"have to start over waiting again (which would lead to a total wait","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time of more than 5 seconds)."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Waits until either ","t